properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued December 31 at 12:49PM MST until January 1 at 11:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...Strong Winds Expected For Wind Prone Locations Into Wednesday
Evening...

The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a High Wind
Warning, which is in effect until 11 AM MST Wednesday.

* WHAT...West winds 30 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65 mph.

* WHERE...Northern Carbon and northern Albany Counties to include
Muddy Gap...Shirley Basin and Medicine Bow.

* WHEN...Through 11 AM Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Travel will be hazardous for
light weight and high profile vehicles, including camping and
tractor trailers. There will be an elevated blow over risk along
Highway 287 north of Rawlins to Muddy Gap as well as north to
south oriented roads near Seminoe Park.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts
of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 AM MST WEDNESDAY
